                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/688: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Nanking</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-19T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 19 [<hi rend="italic">20</hi>], 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. For the Minister. Your May 19, 9 a.m., from Nanking, paragraph 7.</p>
                <p>The Department desires to be informed of the approximate boundaries of the
                    municipal areas at Shanghai, Tientsin, Hankow, and Canton to be shown on the
                    maps which the British intend to submit with Article 16. If possible, give
                    outline by telegram and details by mail despatch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
